			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zelous wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Does any one know how they work?
<br />

<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I've attempted two different LDON raids.  Before I go into details of each specific raid, here's a few general things.
<br />

<br />
-- First, take the maximum number of players you can.  If the limit is 36, take 36.  You can always take less, but it really decreases your chances of winning.  The problem is that your chances of winning are pretty freaking low to begin with.
<br />

<br />
-- Each player on the raid must win 2 adventures at the theme in question.
<br />

<br />
-- As I remember, each raid had a 4 hour time limit.  One hour to buff/get to zone/etc and 3 hours to complete the mission after you zone in.
<br />

<br />
-- The raids have a death limit.  It's like 1.5 or 2 deaths per person.  In every case, this was the real reason that we lost the adventure.  When your pullers bring 3 or 4 1100 quad-hitting mobs into camp and they run amuck over 6k buffed casters, your death limit gets reached quickly.
<br />

<br />
-- On both of these raids, I played my beastlord.  Don't hold that against me, but it gives me a slightly different view of things that playing my mage does.  I'm much more in tune with how hard things hit and how resistant/slowable they are.  For reference, his magelo number is 677060.
<br />

<br />
The first raid that I tried was the Rujark/EC easy raid.  Easy is a bit of a misnomer, as it's tuned to be an elemental level raid.  This was a problem for our raid force, as we were mostly VT/Tier 3 greared.  As I remember, most mobs were yellow to me at 65 and very magic resistant.  We spent an hour or more pulling the entrance mobs and wiping in the first room, then hit the death limit.  This was a rough raid, as most of the pullers, debuffers, and clerics died 4 or 5 times each while the rest of the raid spent time zoning in and out of the entraince to avoid inflating the death numbers.  I don't have any experience in raiding the elemental planes, so I can't really say how the mobs compare to elemental mobs.
<br />

<br />
The second raid I tried was mistmoore/BB easy raid.  This is a VT level raid, so we should have been able to do it.  I LD'd or had computer problems part of the way in, so I never got to see what exactly happened.  The general consensus that I got after I logged back in was that we hit the death limit and lost the raid.  Here's what I can tell you though:  Although the raid was tuned to be VT difficulty, it was very different than a normal VT experience.  The mobs hit significantly harder than Eom's in VT, but had less hp's (and didn't spawn another mob on their death).  So, the challenge was really to get a small pull of mobs (like 2 or 3 at a time) slowed and controlled/offtanked quickly.  If you could do that, the mobs fell easilly.  A slow resist or a missed heal on an offtank usually meant that a shaman or spot healer died, however.<br />_________________<br />Nitim Itoh
<br />
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=363415">Check me out</A></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
